      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I was just trying to make a point about the gravity of the responsibility, but I understand how it might seem unrelated. To answer your question directly, yes, the indemnification clause does suggest that you may be liable for the Disclosing Party's legal fees if you breach the agreement or are found to be negligent. This is because the clause explicitly mentions \"reasonable attorneys' fees\" as part of the damages. However, it's worth noting that the specifics of your liability would depend on the terms of the NDA and the circumstances of the breach. It's always a good idea to carefully review the agreement and seek advice from a lawyer if you're unsure.",
